    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_23131_1834_07_14_page01.jpg"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK"/>London
                        <date when="1834-07-14">July 14. 1834</date></dateline>
                    <salute>
                        <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Dear Miss Edgeworth</persName>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    I have<lb/>
                    received at length a copy<lb/>
                    of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">Helen</title> &amp; must not delay<lb/>
                    &amp; thank you for the pleasantest<lb/>
                    evening that has for many<lb/>
                    a day fallen to my<lb/>
                    lot. I don't believe there<lb/>
                    will be any considerable<lb/>
                    division of opinion about this<lb/>
                    novel - at least I fancy<lb/>
                    they must be terribly<lb/>
                    obtuse folks indeed who<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_23131_1834_07_14_page02.jpg"/>
                    don't perceive the mighty<lb/>
                    gulf between the delicate<lb/>
                    delineation &amp; nicely<lb/>
                    shaded <hi rend="underline">contrasts</hi> of such<lb/>
                    characters as yours &amp;<lb/>
                    the scene painting style<lb/>
                    of even the best of the<lb/>
                    recent adventures in<lb/>
                    this branch of literature.<lb/>
                    May you <unclear>now</unclear> you have found<lb/>
                    that you have at least<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_23131_1834_07_14_page03.jpg"/>
                    lost nothing of the old<lb/>
                    craft be emboldened<lb/>
                    &amp; refuse yourself any<lb/>
                    further pause!<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    May we hope to see you in<lb/>
                    town this season? How<lb/>
                    well you know <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName><lb/>
                    how much better than any<lb/>
                    that live constantly there.<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockS1">Sophia</persName> &amp; the children are<lb/>
                    well &amp; so I trust are all<lb/>
                    under your roof<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_23131_1834_07_14_page04.jpg"/>
                    I am sure they will all be<lb/>
                    made happy by &amp; bye<lb/>
                    with the general<lb/>
                    reception of Miss Helen<lb/>
                    &amp; Miss Edgeworth<lb/>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    Yours most Sincerely<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1"><hi rend="underline">JGLockhart</hi></persName><lb/>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
